type: Tutorial Step - Let's Run the Command!

definition.text: Let's get on with the task at hand! Copy the command below, paste it on the search/command box, and hit Enter!

paragraphs.text: On Windows, a GitHub sign in dialog pops-up offering to authenticate with your token or password. Either should work! Remember that the latest version of Git is required! If you have issues with the latest version, restarting the PC may help. On Mac, it is the Terminal that asks for credentials. If you enabled two-factor authentication on GitHub, use the token even if asked for the password!
